<p>
<seg id=2> Yongjiang Gu expressed that, economic developments in the mainland provided five great opportunities for Hong Kong. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> ___Bringing lasting prosperity and steady economic growth to Hong Kong. </seg>
<seg id=4> The economic growth in the mainland has been continuing and steady. Hong Kong's economy will be benefit from this economic vitality in the mainland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> ____Providing more trading opportunities for Hong Kong. </seg>
<seg id=6> With the step-by-step opening up in the services industry of the mainland, Hong Kong services industry will be able to expand into the developing areas. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> ____Enhancing Hong Kong as a trade and shipping business center. </seg>
<seg id=8> By the year 2010, the total amount of foreign trade in the mainland is predicted to reach 800 million US dollars. There is no doubt that the demands of using Hong Kong as a shipping center will increase. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> ____Enhancing the development of the financial market in Hong Kong. </seg>
<seg id=10> With the further reforms in the government-owned enterprises, there will be more joint-stock companies that go on the overseas stock market. Hong Kong is going to be the first place for these government-owned enterprises to go on the market. </seg>
<seg id=11> As a result, the developments in the Hong Kong stock market will result in an enlarged scope for Hong Kong stocks and result in an improved structure of the Hong Kong stock market.  Hong Kong also will be able to obtain more funds from China.  All of this will result in strengthening and enhancing Hong Kong's position as an International Financial center. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> ____Strengthening the international capacity of Hong Kong products. </seg>
<seg id=13> Because of the complementary relationship between the mainland and Hong Kong, and the combination of the advantages in both places, the international capacity of Hong Kong products will be strengthened. </seg>
</p>
